        <h1>London is your Oyster with great deals across the Capital</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        02 August 2006
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Oyster card holders can now enjoy the best of London with a wide range of fantastic two for one deals at the city's top shows, attractions and restaurants during August and September.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p> Transport for London (TfL) has teamed up with a number of major entertainment locations so Oyster holders can take advantage of a range of deals.</p>
<p>Mayor of London, Ken Livingstone, said: "Oyster card is the simplest, cheapest and fastest way to get around London on public transport. </p>
<p>"These new two for one deals at London's top attractions mean there has never been a better time to get an Oyster card."</p>
<p>The two for one deals include: </p>
<ul>
<li>Attractions - London Eye River Experience, Jongleurs Comedy Club 
</li><li>West End shows - The Producers, Sinatra, We Will Rock You, Blood Brothers, Les Miserables, The Canterbury Tales, Footloose, Seven Brides for Seven Brothers, Daddy Cool, Stomp 
</li><li>Restaurants - Bangra Beat, Spaghetti House (Sicilian Avenue, St Martin's Lane), Est Est Est (Chiswick,) and Imli Restaurant 
</li><li>Royal Philharmonic Orchestra performances at the Royal Albert Hall 
</li><li>Outdoor concerts across the capital including Jools Holland and Westlife</li></ul>
<p>Full details of the deals and how to take advantage of them are available <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/oyster ">online</a> where people can also buy an Oyster card.<br></p>
            <ul>
<li>The Oyster campaign began on 1 August with the majority of deals ending on 30 September - for full terms and conditions visit <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/oyster">www.tfl.gov.uk/oyster</a> or pick up a leaflet available at all London Underground stations</li></ul>

     

        
        
        
